  28 Mar 2007; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> :
  Stable for HPPA too.

  18 Mar 2007; Steve Dibb <beandog@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.40.0.ebuild:
  amd64 stable

  12 Mar 2007; Raúl Porcel <armin76@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.40.0.ebuild:
  x86 stable

  29 Jan 2007; Bryan Østergaard <kloeri@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.40.0.ebuild:
  Add ~alpha + ~ia64 keywords.

*wavpack-4.40.0 (26 Dec 2006)

  26 Dec 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> +wavpack-4.40.0.ebuild:
  Version bump.

  20 Dec 2006; Gustavo Zacarias <gustavoz@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.31.ebuild:
  Stable on sparc

  05 Dec 2006; Jeroen Roovers <jer@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.31.ebuild:
  Marked ~hppa (bug #155961).

  24 Nov 2006; Markus Rothe <corsair@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.31.ebuild:
  Added ~ppc64; bug #155961

  22 Nov 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.31.ebuild:
  Add ~x86-fbsd keyword.

  29 Oct 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.1.ebuild,
  wavpack-4.2.ebuild:
  Fix autotools rebuilding, thanks to Patrick Lauer in bug #153359.

  14 Jun 2006; Jon Hood <squinky86@gentoo.org> wavpack-4.1.ebuild,
  wavpack-4.31.ebuild:
  Mark 4.31 stable on amd64, as 4.1 does not work in 64-bit mode. Marking 4.1
  -amd64. #132759. Thanks to Jonas Berlin <xkr47@outerspace.dyndns.org> for
  finding this one.

*wavpack-4.31 (19 Mar 2006)

  19 Mar 2006; Stefan Briesenick <sbriesen@gentoo.org> +wavpack-4.31.ebuild:
  ebuild cleanup, version bump. solving bug #112003.

  08 Jan 2006; Diego Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org> metadata.xml:
  Remove retiring dev from metadata.

*wavpack-4.2 (29 Apr 2005)

  29 Apr 2005; Jan Brinkmann <luckyduck@gentoo.org> -wavpack-4.0.ebuild,
